title: 2008 Michigan Republican Primary votes by county, USA, 2008
name: 2008 Michigan Republican Primary votes by county, USA, 2008
description: These maps are based on the Michigan Secretary of State Election Website (1) as of 10 minutes past Midnight, January 16, 2008. These are uncertified" results. This is Romney's first win and probably saved him from dropping out of the primaries after finishing 2nd the GOP has no clear cut front runner. Look for an updated vote count a little later in the day.  Romney got nearly 39% votes (~337850),  to McCain's 30% (257200),  followed by Huckabee at 16% (~139700). Note: Two counties, namely Monroe and Oscoda, out of 83 do not have vote count available yet.  both in Iowa and New Hampshire. McCain and Huckabee finished 2nd and 3rd respectively.
